profile_positions.description:
Growth is one of the values of HRG. Hospitality is a fast paced industry where employees is a key. Learning and development is crucial as this is the only way we can reach all our goals. 
Where to find me?
Ramada by Wyndham Amsterdam Airport 
Mövenpick Amsterdam City Centre 
Ibis Styles Ahoy Rotterdam 
Mövenpick The Hague 
Mövenpick Den Bosch 
Amedia Amsterdam Airport

- joined the company at a post-covid stage;
- actively helped with (re) building the team using new approaches in recruitment;
- redesigned, updated brand training programs;
- created onboarding program and e-learning paths per department. 
- delivered trainings upon needs of employees and managers and using analytics of RPS per property;
- implemented, standardised and monitored mandatory training of a brand and horeca;
- created programs of engaging, recognition and motivation of employees;
- improved employee life circle.

•	Decreasing of 32% employee turnover by development and implementation of a staff adaptation system and motivation, controlling an execution of the system by managers;
•	reduction of 20% labor costs by analytic work with staff's shifts, payrolls; optimization of staff;
•	reduction of 20% HR expenses through projects of changing a place of a staff house, changing the system of transportation (sharing expenses between the company and staff);
•	provision of the labor law related matters; elaboration of local standards and control of following them by staff, update of job descriptions due to the market changes, absence management;
•	creating corporative projects which help to increase the loyalty of staff to the company, as regular meetings with a celebration of success of each person, involve staff to top up the popularity of the hotels on the Internet etc;
•	creating the system of trainings for every level of staff: welcome training, service trainings, master trainings; trainings for management team; 
•	controlling the operation processes of hotels: renovation of the restaurant's interior and menu, changing of the system of rooms cleaning, a transition to outsourcing staff.

My personal achievements:
▪ created a new structure of the HR department with controlling all working processes in hotels;
▪ created the HR brand which is popular in Sochi and close regions;
▪ successfully passed the verification of the labor inspection;
▪ got the position of HR Director after starting my work as a training manager;
▪ got the reward of "The Best Manager 2018".

The full cycle of organization of work of the recreation center: 
- control of the quality of service, including control and prevention of technical issues;
- recruitment and trainings; 
- work with corporate and individual clients - special request, group accommodation; 
- organization of corporate events and banquets; 
- organization of the cafe on the territory of the base (personnel, purchase of products, accounting);
- maintaining primary accounting and reporting documentation; 
- marketing and advertisement.

- communication with all departments of the hotel to make accommodation comfortable;
- trainings for receptionists (service, upsells, anti-stress);
- control of all operation departments during night shifts and weekends;
- booking, control payment, check-in/check-out; communication with guests;
- daily financial reports.
